Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Per Order of the Presiding Judge, Misdemeanor Division, this motion/request is hereby assigned to Judge Christopher Dee, Br. 37, for review. mag
DOC request to review order for sentence credit.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:

The Court ordered defendant to serve 60 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 27 (twenty-seven) days time served, STRAIGHT TIME.  

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and fees by March 17, 2017, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.

Defendant Marian Marquis Moore in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Defendant Marian Marquis Moore in custody at MSDF.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

Attorney Francisco Araiza in court, defendant Marian Marquis Moore not in court, in custody.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 37.  Stipulated request for adjournment received and filed.  Plea hearing scheduled for September 17, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Marian Marquis Moore in court with attorney Alexis B Stewart.  Defendant Marian Marquis Moore in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 11, 2015 at 08:30 am.
